value: * Count the number of
* matched workers per plant of various groups:
* by education, experience, MNE/nonMNEexperience, new
* Count the total years of education, experience and
* wages of each of these groups.
* These variables are saved in new_workers.dta.
* To be used to construct various plant level shares
* used in plant level productivity regressions.
*quietly replace education=1 if education==0
*drop if realwage<12000 | realwage==.
*gen isic4=int(naering/10)
* Define separations= all workers in year t and plant x
* that are not in plant x in year t+1
* last year in panel all workers are separated from plant x in t
* Define plant turnoverrate=separations_t/employment_t
* Count # of ind per plant and by educationtype

varlist.value: " # of full time workers in the plant"
"# of full time workers in the plant with education=`t'"

value: * Count # of ind per plant by educationyears

varlist.value: "# of full time workers in the plant with years of educ=`t'"

value: * Generate accumulated recent experience from allMNE, dom and for MNE
* New: Indicator for being a new worker in the plant, new defined as
* being new in t, t-1 or t-2, (those with MNE exp from t-1,2,3) are by def
* new in non-MNEs either in t, t-1 or t-2

varlist.value: "=1 if worker is new to plant in t, t-1 or t-2"

value: * If new and no MNE experience, generate indicator for nonMNEexp

varlist.value: "=1 if new ftw with exp from nonMNE"

value: * For those with MNEexp, count this only if they are new to the plant
* For those with exp from large plants, count this only if they are new to the plant
* and without MNEexp
* Number of new workers with experience from MNEs t-4-t-5

varlist.value: "=1 if MNE exp in t-4 and t-5 and not after"
"=1 if new and MNE exp in t-4 and t-5 and not after"

value: * Count number of new workers with each type of experience

varlist.value: "# of new workers in plant with recent exp from `t'"
"# workers with MNEexp t-4 t-5 and not after"
"# new workers with MNEexp t-4 t-5 and not after"

value: * Count number of new workers with each type of experience by education type/year

varlist.value: "# of new ftw in plant with educ=`t' & exp=`z'"
"# of new ftw in plant with eduy=`t' & exp=`z'"

value: * Count number of new workers with MNEexperience from the same 3 digit sector
* Do this by generating indicator for being new from the same 3 digit sector

varlist.value: "=1 if new ftw that comes from same 3ds"

value: * For those with MNEexp, count this only if they are new to the plant from same 3ds

varlist.value: "=1 if new ftw with MNE exp from same 3ds"
"# of new ftw with recent MNEexp from same 3ds"
"# of new ftw with recent MNEexp outside same 3ds"

value: * Total experience, education and wages for all groups of workers defined above

* Count # of ind per plant by education/experience groups

varlist.value: "# of ftw in plant with years of educ=`t' & erf<5"
"# of new ftw in plant with eduy=`t' & exp=`z' & erf<5"

value: * Keep one observation per plant and year:

varlist.value: "# of ftw in plant with years of educ=`t' & erf<10"
"# of new ftw in plant with eduy=`t' & exp=`z' & erf<10"

value: * Keep one observation per plant and year:

varlist.value: "# of ftw in plant with years of educ=`t' & erf>=10"
"# of new ftw in plant with eduy=`t' & exp=`z' & erf>=10"
